            <h4>What to do within 7 days?</h4>
            <div class="donts_list_3">
                <div class="donts_item color_2">
                    <p><span>✅</span>  Sun the car</p>
                    <img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0234/7089/9277/files/Rectangle_576_12.png?v=1764769390" alt="" />
                    <div class="info_line">
                        <img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0234/7089/9277/files/Group_1256.png?v=1764762400" alt=""/>
                        Dab the car dry with a microfiber cloth (no wiping) to avoid marks.
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="donts_item color_1">
                    <p><span>⚠️</span> Avoid car wash and rain</p>
                    <img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0234/7089/9277/files/Rectangle_576_13.png?v=1764769390" alt="" />
                    <div class="info_line">
                        <img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0234/7089/9277/files/Group_1256.png?v=1764762400" alt=""/>
                        Avoid washing or exposing the car to rain for the next 7 days to allow the PPF to fully cure. This ensures long-lasting protection.
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="donts_item color_1">
                    <p><span>⚠️</span> Avoid driving fast</p>
                    <img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0234/7089/9277/files/Rectangle_576_14.png?v=1764769390" alt="" />
                    <div class="info_line">
                        <img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0234/7089/9277/files/Group_1256.png?v=1764762400" alt=""/>
                        High speeds can cause strong wind pressure, potentially lifting the PPF edges.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <h4>What you may experience within 7 days?</h4>
            <div class="donts_list immediately_list">
                <div class="donts_item color_1">
                    <p><span>⚠️</span>  Milky / Hazy appearance</p>
                    <img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0234/7089/9277/files/Rectangle_576_15.png?v=1764769390" alt="" />
                    <div class="info_line">
                        <img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0234/7089/9277/files/Group_1256.png?v=1764762400" alt=""/>
                        Park your car under the hot sun for 7 days. The air bubbles and haziness will disappear once the tint fully dries.
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="donts_item color_1">
                    <p><span>⚠️</span>Warped edges (Lifting)</p>
                    <img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0234/7089/9277/files/Rectangle_576_16.png?v=1764769390" alt="" />
                    <div class="info_line">
                        <img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0234/7089/9277/files/Group_1256.png?v=1764762400" alt=""/>
                        PPF edges may lift if the car is driven in wind or rain before fully drying. Don’t worry—just bring it back to us, and we’ll fix it for you.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
